<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A woman has died in a horror crash between a sports car and truck in Sydney's south in wet conditions.</p>

<p>Emergency services were called to the intersection of Coward and Bourke streets in Mascot following the collision around 12.30pm on Wednesday.</p>

<p>A NSW Ambulance spokesman told Daily Mail Australia a critically injured middle-aged woman was trapped inside the Ford Mustang GT for a short time but died at the scene, despite paramedics' desperate efforts to save her.</p>

<p>Investigations are continuing after a fatal crash between a car and truck in Mascot</p>

<p>Police remain at the crash scene at the intersection of Coward and Bourke streets</p>

<p>The truck driver suffered minor injuries and was taken to Prince of Wales Hospital for mandatory blood and alcohol testing.</p>

<p>The Ford Mustang GT involved is valed at $64,000.</p>

<p>Police are investigating the circumstances surrounding the crash and remain at the scene.</p>

<p>Motorists are urged to avoid the area as several roads remain closed.</p>

<p>A middle-aged woman was trapped inside the car and died at the scene</p>

<p>'Take care in the area &amp; allow extra travel time,' a Live Traffic Sydney alert states.</p>

<p>'All westbound lanes are now closed on Coward St between O'Riordan St &amp; Bourke St. Avoid the area or use an alternative route. One eastbound lane is also closed. Traffic in the area is heavy.'</p>

<p>Bus routes 357, 400, 418 and 420 have also been diverted.</p>

<p>A report will be prepared for the Coroner.</p>

<p>Police speak to shocked witnesses at the scene in Mascot on Wednesday afternoon</p>
